1. Nastavićemo razgovor kada se formira nova vlada. (*formira* - present tense, third person singular) (We will continue the conversation when the new government is formed.)
2. Oni su ispunili sve *forme* za registraciju kompanije. (*forme* - plural, accusative case) (They have completed all the forms for registering the company.)
3. Ova knjiga je napisana u *formi* romana. (*formi* - singular, locative case) (This book is written in the form of a novel.)
4. Svi učesnici moraju popuniti prijavnu *formu*. (*formu* - singular, accusative case) (All participants must fill out the registration form.)
5. Iako ne volim da pevam, pokušaću da *formiram* bend. (*formiram* - present tense, first person singular) (Although I don't like to sing, I will try to form a band.)
6. Glumac se mora *formirati* pre predstave. (*formirati* - infinitive) (The actor must prepare before the performance.)
7. *Formiranje* nove političke stranke je u toku. (*formiranje* - noun, singular, nominative case) (The formation of a new political party is underway.)
8. Ona je učestvovala u *formiranju* udruženja za zaštitu životinja. (*formiranju* - noun, singular, locative case) (She participated in the formation of an association for the protection of animals.)
9. Rezultati istraživanja će biti *formalno* objavljeni u naučnom časopisu. (*formalno* - adverb) (The research results will be formally published in a scientific journal.)
10. Njihov plan je da *reformišu* zdravstveni sistem. (*reformišu* - present tense, third person plural) (Their plan is to reform the healthcare system.)